<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16148&amp;p=199146#p199146"><![CDATA[
Since they are passive devices (no electronics inside) only possible thing stopping insertion into USA machine is plastic moulding. The &quot;Fire SNES game converter&quot; that I got has no plastic where the stoppers are in USA SNES cartslot and will fit and the Datel thing has slots in same places as real USA game carts so it will also fit in the slot of a USA SNES.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3483">TmEE</a> — Tue Jun 27, 2017 5:05 pm</p><hr />
